      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Parse receipts with Google Drive and Google Sheets and log the results\n\n**Pattern:** File Processing · **Level:** Advanced · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nParse receipts with Google Drive and Google Sheets and log the results. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual contracts is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nHourly Schedule → Download from Google Drive → Parse CSV Contents → Clean & Reshape Rows → Rows Pass Validation? → Load Rows into Google Sheets → Repack as XLSX → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to file processing without manual effort\n- Anyone automating contracts in legal\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Improves response time\n- Saves hours of manual work each week\n- Scales without extra headcount\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: Google OAuth2; Google OAuth2 / service account; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "ee9e3b92-c31a-a612-64ae-dc2ac128a7aa",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
